## Recent Decisions
- 2026-03-19T20:40:28.272Z | **Introduce deterministic smart spec updater workflow**: Use structured spec-update records plus rule-based routing and safe patch application so spec drift can be reviewed and applied without destructive rewrites.
- 2026-03-19T20:35:39.056Z | **Make init idempotent with lightweight specs and agent scaffold**: Re-running init should safely create only missing files and report skipped items; lightweight templates keep onboarding useful without heavy process overhead.
- 2026-03-19T20:13:12.690Z | **Model run review as explicit state transitions with task updates**: Treating review outcomes (approved/needs_changes/blocked/merged) as first-class run metadata closes the loop from execution to acceptance while keeping follow-up task creation structured and repeatable.
- 2026-03-19T20:08:51.509Z | **Use mission-control board + dual detail panels for task/run visibility**: A board/list with task and run detail panes provides high-signal execution visibility while keeping actions and status filters in one operational surface.
- 2026-03-19T20:04:09.616Z | **Use explicit rule-based orchestration for task assignment and queueing**: A deterministic rules engine keeps assignment behavior understandable and overridable while enforcing dependency gates before starting ready tasks.
- 2026-03-19T19:57:56.964Z | **Introduce runner adapter abstraction for sidecar run**: Separating runner prepare/execute/collectResult behind adapters keeps CLI thin and enables future real Codex/Claude command integration without changing run orchestration.
- 2026-03-19T18:18:11.806Z | **Compile prompts from task packets into per-run markdown briefs**: A deterministic template-based compiler keeps prompts readable and stable while linking each prompt to a run record for execution traceability.
- 2026-03-19T17:43:48.297Z | **Separate task packets from run records**: Task packets represent durable intent while run records capture each execution attempt; separate storage under .sidecar/runs enables multiple attempts and clean task-to-runs querying.

